
---

## PART 13 — Android Kotlin Starter (Jetpack Compose) — outline + key files

I’ll provide a minimal starter that subscribes to STOMP (via `okhttp` WebSocket) and shows markers on a map (Mapbox or Google Maps). Here I give the basic Gradle config and a main Activity to connect to the backend — full Android app build can be done in Android Studio.

### `android-client/build.gradle.kts` (excerpt)

```kotlin
plugins {
    id("com.android.application")
    kotlin("android")
}

android {
    compileSdk = 34
    defaultConfig {
        applicationId = "com.example.flighttracker"
        minSdk = 24
        targetSdk = 34
        versionCode = 1
        versionName = "1.0"
    }
    buildFeatures { compose = true }
    composeOptions { kotlinCompilerExtensionVersion = "1.6.0" }
}

dependencies {
    implementation("androidx.core:core-ktx:1.12.0")
    implementation("androidx.compose.ui:ui:1.6.0")
    implementation("androidx.compose.material:material:1.6.0")
    implementation("com.squareup.okhttp3:okhttp:4.10.0")
    implementation("com.google.android.gms:play-services-maps:18.1.0") // or Mapbox
}
